condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Agreements between PGR and co-executing agencies | Description :Sch. 2, Section I, B.1 - under Parts 1, 2 and 3of the Project, the Recipient, through PGR, shall enter into separate agreements (each a “Co-execution Agreement”), under terms andconditions satisfactory to the Association, with the respective Co-executing Agencyto address its respective role in theimplementation of the pertinent Project activity, all as set forth in the Operational Manual. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Agreements between PGR and participating municipalities | Description :Sch. 2, Section I, B.2 - Prior to thecarrying out of any Project activity under Parts 1, 2, and 3 of the Project in any given Participating Municipality, the Recipientshall, through PGR, enter into an agreement (“Participation Agreement”) with each such municipality under terms and conditionssatisfactory to the Association, to address the roles of the participating municipalities | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Establishment of the PCU, CIP and CTO | Description :Sch. 2, Section I, A.1 - The Recipient shall operate andmaintain, at all times during Project implementation, the Project Coordination Unit (PCU), the Inter-institutional Committee (CIP)and the Operational Technical Committee (CTO) with a structure, functions, responsibilities and adequate resources, allsatisfactory to the Association. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Retroactive Financing | Description :Sch. 2, Section IV, B.1 (a) - (i) an aggregate amount not to exceed 20% ofthe amount allocated to Category (1) may be made for payments made prior to the date of this Agreement but on or after August 31,2012; or (ii) an aggregate amount not to exceed 40% of theamount allocated to Category (2) may be made for payments made prior tothis date but on or after August 31, 2012 | Due Date :31-Aug-2012

Finance Agreement :Safeguard Instruments | Description :Sch. 2, Section I, D.1 - The Recipient, through PGR, shall carry out theProject in accordance with the provisions of the EA, the EMP, the Process Framework and the IPP, as applicable. The Recipient,through the PGR, shall not assign, amend, abrogate, or waive the EA, the EMP, the Process Framework, and/or the IPP, or anyprovision thereof, without prior approval of the Association. | Frequency :Monthly

Finance Agreement :Sch. 2, Section V, 1 - Procurement Audits | Description :The Recipient, through PGR, shall: (i) have all theprocurement records and documentation of the Project audited each fiscal year during Project implementation, in accordance withappropriate procurement audit principles, by independent auditors acceptable to theAssociation | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Sch. 2, Section V, 2 - Poverty Measurement Survey | Description :The Recipient undertakes to carry out theactivities under Part 1.C(i) of Schedule 1 of this Agreement in accordance with international best practices, acceptable to theAssociation. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, A.1 | Description :The recipient shall operate and maintain at all times during Projectimplementation, the PCU, CIP and CTO with a structure, functions, responsibilities and adequate resources, all satisfactory to theAssociation. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, D.1 | Description :The Recipient, through PGR, shall carry out the Project in accordancewith the provisions of the EA, the EMP, the Process Framework, and the IPP, as applicable. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS
